  "body": "[Equation (53)](https://github.com/ethereum/yellowpaper/blob/master/Paper.tex#L466) refers to the minimum gas limit for blocks as 125000. Should this value be changed to 5000 (0x1388)? Various Ethereum clients seem to be using that minimum gas limit value:\r\n* *Geth*: https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/master/params/protocol_params.go#L68\r\n* *Parity*: https://github.com/paritytech/parity/blob/master/ethcore/res/ethereum/foundation.json#L146",
